Courage: noun
mental or moral strength to venture, persevere, and withstand danger, fear, or difficulty

Definition of encourage
transitive verb
1a : to inspire with courage, spirit, or hope : HEARTEN
b : to attempt to persuade :HEARTEN

2 : to spur on : STIMULATE

3 : to give help or patronage to : FOSTER

If courage is what we need, what do you do to find encouragement? I think one of the best ways is to be an encourager yourself. When you encourage others, your words will make an impression on you too. 

The other day, the kids were learning about respect and self-respect in their taekwando class. We talked about it afterward and went over some examples of self-respect. That’s when it hit me that all the things I say about self-respect are useless if I don’t model it for them. Encouraging them to have self-respect gave me courage to make some changes in my own life and respect myself more. 

Do you have an example of offering encouragement to someone else helped you find your own courage? #courage #scripture #faith";}i:160;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:161;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:0;}i:162;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEuXDcWgttK";}i:163;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:259:"https://scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/s1080x1080/118878824_739180370197755_2053521091382330080_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=103&_nc_ohc=a3og5K1Hwl0AX8gMLst&_nc_tp=15&oh=c0b66ee5364e82af4fd975ec054d3a39&oe=5F7C80A3";}i:164;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:165;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:3408812962;}i:166;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:167;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:168;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:169;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2390949730003371909";}i:170;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEuXByUqseF";}i:171;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599243440;}i:172;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:431:"Always remember ☝🏽 God gives his hardest battles to his strongest soldiers!
